snippet.textDisplay: For the dice stacking, it works because centrifugal force is acting on the dice throwing them to the sides of the glass, not possible for them to stay in the centre. they get thrown to the top of the glass and then stack at the top of the glass. Then they are moving together at the same speed and hitting the same spots, after that they are stacked in a fixed position so when you stop moving the glass on a flat surface they are stacked. That is how dice stacking works.
